---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="DonateCrate Neighborhood Rollout"
  description="See how DonateCrate launches neighborhood-by-neighborhood to keep pickup routes dense and reliable."
>
  <main class="simple-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
    <span class="eyebrow">Neighborhood Rollout</span>
    <h1>We grow one strong service area at a time.</h1>
    <p class="simple-page__lede">
      DonateCrate launches in focused service pockets first so pickup windows stay reliable, route density stays strong,
      and the experience stays worth using.
    </p>
    <div class="simple-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>Active Launch Area</h2>
        <p>Current rollout is centered on the Knoxville `37922` anchor zone with nearby eligible addresses.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Pending Areas</h2>
        <p>Addresses near active routes may show as pending while we build enough demand for a clean monthly schedule.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Expansion Signal</h2>
        <p>Waitlist volume, nearby route coverage, and service quality all shape where we open next.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <section class="feature-band">
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Why this matters</span>
        <h2>Better route planning means a better customer experience.</h2>
        <p>We would rather open the next neighborhood well than overpromise citywide coverage before the pickup experience is ready.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">If you are not active yet</span>
        <h2>The waitlist helps move your area forward.</h2>
        <p>Joining the waitlist tells us where people want pickup most and helps us prioritize the next expansion decision.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
